WEBVTT

00:04.710 --> 00:07.420
♪ Magic is real here ♪

00:07.500 --> 00:10.340
♪ Far away from home ♪

00:10.420 --> 00:12.130
♪ Anything can happen ♪

00:12.220 --> 00:15.220
♪ When witches make the rules ♪

00:15.300 --> 00:17.600
♪ Monsters are cool ♪

00:17.680 --> 00:20.810
♪ The moon is our friend ♪

00:20.890 --> 00:22.930
♪ I want to stay with you ♪

00:23.020 --> 00:27.440
♪ On Summer Camp Island ♪

00:27.520 --> 00:32.650
♪♪

00:32.740 --> 00:36.660
<i>I'm really sorry, everyone,</i>
<i>but I can't do this jump.</i>

00:36.740 --> 00:39.030
Not with a broken heart.

00:39.120 --> 00:40.790
Teammate:<i> But, Ski Bat,</i>
<i>you have to!</i>

00:40.870 --> 00:42.200
<i>No pressure, but, like,</i>

00:42.290 --> 00:44.080
<i>the whole school</i>
<i>is counting on you, dude.</i>

00:44.160 --> 00:47.630
Ski Bat:<i> Counting on me</i>
<i>was their first mistake.</i>

00:47.710 --> 00:49.710
Melanie:<i> But it won't be</i>
<i>their last.</i>

00:49.790 --> 00:50.300
[ Gasps ]

00:50.380 --> 00:51.710
[ Gasps ]

00:51.800 --> 00:53.720
I thought your parents
were renewing their vows.

00:53.800 --> 00:55.550
They are,
but I told them

00:55.630 --> 00:58.260
I have to give my boyfriend
something.

00:58.340 --> 00:59.510
What?

00:59.600 --> 01:00.970
This.

01:01.060 --> 01:02.270
[ Giggling ]

01:02.350 --> 01:03.480
Ski Bat!

01:03.560 --> 01:04.810
[ Giggling ]

01:04.890 --> 01:05.980
[ Whoosh ]

01:07.060 --> 01:09.310
Whoo-hoo!
Yeah, Ski Bat!
Ski Bat!

01:09.400 --> 01:11.690
Awesome.

01:13.110 --> 01:15.780
Okay, everyone.
That was "Ski Bat."

01:15.860 --> 01:17.490
Selected by Max
to celebrate

01:17.570 --> 01:19.370
him discovering
that he's a vampire.

01:19.450 --> 01:20.410
-Whoo-hoo!
-Yeah, Max!

01:20.490 --> 01:21.990
-Yes!
-Nice job, Max!

01:22.080 --> 01:24.330
Does everyone get
something like this
when they find out?

01:24.410 --> 01:26.660
Depends on what kind
of magical creature you are.

01:26.750 --> 01:29.540
Shark told me during
a one-on-one therapy session.

01:29.630 --> 01:31.000
Oh.

01:31.090 --> 01:33.300
Don't feel bad, Oliver.
You'll figure out yours soon.

01:33.380 --> 01:35.420
Magical identities
are always a mystery.

01:35.510 --> 01:36.970
Well,
not for Susie.

01:37.050 --> 01:39.090
She plans these events.
I think she already knows

01:39.180 --> 01:41.680
what every camper's
magical identity is.

01:41.760 --> 01:43.600
Reeeeally?

01:43.680 --> 01:45.270
Susie: Listen to this,
Jimjams --

01:45.350 --> 01:47.020
"Despite the creative
shortcomings

01:47.100 --> 01:49.850
of Vampire Video's
stale initiation rituals,

01:49.940 --> 01:52.440
the event was yet
another technical masterpiece

01:52.520 --> 01:53.940
and deserves praise."

01:54.030 --> 01:55.320
Aw, that's nice.

01:55.400 --> 01:56.820
Ah, soldiers and eggs!

01:56.900 --> 01:59.030
Does it get any better
than this, Jimjams?

01:59.110 --> 02:00.200
Nope.

02:00.280 --> 02:01.320
Ahhh --
[ Knock on door ]

02:01.410 --> 02:02.780
Hm?

02:02.870 --> 02:04.450
I want to know
my magical identity.

02:04.540 --> 02:05.290
[ Door slams ]

02:05.370 --> 02:07.040
Please, Susie!

02:07.120 --> 02:09.420
[ Groans ]

02:09.500 --> 02:11.130
I hate not knowing!

02:11.210 --> 02:13.040
I wanna be finished!
Cooked!

02:13.130 --> 02:14.880
Like a turkey
on Thanksgiving Day!

02:14.960 --> 02:17.420
Well, you gotta marinate
a little more, buddy.

02:17.510 --> 02:18.880
I'm not telling you
what you are.

02:18.970 --> 02:20.720
Then you have left me
no choice.

02:20.800 --> 02:22.720
I will get you to tell me
by participating

02:22.800 --> 02:25.770
in the age-old tradition
of nonviolent protest.

02:25.850 --> 02:27.350
A sit-in!

02:27.430 --> 02:28.520
Where may I sit?

02:28.600 --> 02:30.600
[ Groans ]
Wherever you want.

02:30.690 --> 02:34.570
You would not believe my ability
to ignore precocious activism.

02:34.650 --> 02:36.400
Nonviolently
sitting down.

02:36.480 --> 02:38.150
Nonviolently
crossing arms.

02:38.240 --> 02:40.610
Ahhh --
Nonviolently waiting
for you to tell me

02:40.700 --> 02:42.910
what kind of
magical creature I am.

02:42.990 --> 02:44.410
[ Sighs ]

02:44.490 --> 02:46.790
Oliver, having questions in life
is actually a great thing.

02:46.870 --> 02:48.450
It's the fuel
that keeps us moving.

02:48.540 --> 02:49.750
Know what I mean?

02:49.830 --> 02:50.960
No.

02:52.040 --> 02:53.380
Jimjams, what do I do?

02:53.460 --> 02:55.500
I can't tell him.
With this group, he's gotta have

02:55.590 --> 02:57.710
some kind of epiphany
or something.
Hmm.

02:57.800 --> 02:59.880
Well, in my bowling league
back home,

02:59.970 --> 03:01.590
when the rookies
were getting impatient,

03:01.680 --> 03:04.550
we'd put up the gutter bumpers
to help guide the ball in.

03:04.640 --> 03:06.760
Maybe all Oliver needs
is a little bump.

03:06.850 --> 03:08.060
A little guidance.

03:08.140 --> 03:09.730
Like the ball.

03:09.810 --> 03:11.100
Oliver is the ball.

03:11.190 --> 03:12.900
Like from my
bowling league.
Yeah, got it.

03:12.980 --> 03:14.110
A little guidance.

03:14.190 --> 03:15.520
Come on,
Abbie Hoffman.

03:15.610 --> 03:17.030
You're gonna take your sit-in
on the road.

03:17.110 --> 03:18.440
I gotta run
some errands.

03:18.530 --> 03:19.780
A nomadic sit-in...

03:19.860 --> 03:21.610
I can do that.

03:22.820 --> 03:25.950
Wait, what's this?
Late fee?

03:26.030 --> 03:27.910
It says,
"Return Saturday."

03:27.990 --> 03:30.000
It's not<i> any</i> Saturday,
Susie.

03:30.080 --> 03:32.080
It's the Saturday
after you checked it out.

03:32.170 --> 03:34.500
And how am I supposed
to know that?!

03:34.580 --> 03:36.880
I'm not good
with conflict.

03:36.960 --> 03:38.760
"The Tiny Outburst Club"?

03:40.510 --> 03:43.590
Aw, I was hoping there'd be
a secret room or something.

03:43.680 --> 03:45.470
[ Sighs ]

03:45.550 --> 03:48.140
♪♪

03:48.220 --> 03:49.640
Whoa.

03:49.720 --> 03:52.640
♪♪

03:52.730 --> 03:54.730
Blanche: According to this
older translation

03:54.810 --> 03:56.610
of this particular
cypher,

03:56.690 --> 03:58.730
it's not
"heat plus liquid" --

03:58.820 --> 04:02.780
it's "heat plus juice."

04:02.860 --> 04:05.570
Heat plus juice?

04:05.660 --> 04:07.990
I believe the ingredient
we're looking for

04:08.080 --> 04:09.660
is hot sauce.

04:09.740 --> 04:10.830
[ Oliver clears throat ]

04:10.910 --> 04:12.580
Oh! Hi.
Eh, sorry.

04:12.660 --> 04:13.830
Oh, it's you!

04:13.920 --> 04:15.170
What are you guys
doing?

04:15.250 --> 04:17.500
We're debating
the Elixir of Immortality

04:17.590 --> 04:18.840
with these glasses.

04:18.920 --> 04:20.710
You can only talk
if you're wearing them,

04:20.800 --> 04:23.300
and once you're done,
you have to pass them.

04:23.380 --> 04:24.470
It's a "Glass Pass."

04:24.550 --> 04:25.760
Oh, yeah!

04:25.840 --> 04:28.100
To prevent people
from talking over each other.

04:28.180 --> 04:30.470
A-ha-ha-ha!
This guy gets it.

04:30.560 --> 04:32.770
I've always believed
in respectful discourse.

04:32.850 --> 04:35.350
It's nice to meet others
that feel as strongly as I do.

04:35.440 --> 04:37.610
You know, Oliver,
only monsters

04:37.690 --> 04:39.520
are allowed to wear
these glasses.

04:39.610 --> 04:41.190
Would you like
to try them on?

04:41.280 --> 04:43.190
I would, but, uh,
I'm trying to get

04:43.280 --> 04:46.280
Susie to tell me what kind
of magical creature I am.

04:46.360 --> 04:49.160
Anyway, I should
probably get going.

04:49.240 --> 04:51.200
Bye!

04:51.290 --> 04:52.580
Iunno.
Huh?

04:53.960 --> 04:56.620
Ooh! We're doing errands
at Heartforde?

04:56.710 --> 04:58.380
I heart Heartforde!

04:58.460 --> 05:00.630
Everyone hearts Heartforde,
Oliver.

05:00.710 --> 05:03.510
That's why it's
on the sweatshirt.

05:03.590 --> 05:04.970
Piano Tuner?

05:05.050 --> 05:06.050
Uh, alright.

05:06.130 --> 05:07.930
[ Door opens, bell jingles ]
Hm?

05:09.350 --> 05:11.850
[ Discordant notes ]

05:11.930 --> 05:14.890
Wow, it's so great to be back
at the Piano Tuner,

05:14.980 --> 05:16.640
where I come often.

05:16.730 --> 05:18.900
Isn't that right,
Piano Tuner?

05:18.980 --> 05:21.480
The Piano Tuner
is on her lunch break.

05:21.570 --> 05:23.570
Also, I've never
seen you before.

05:23.650 --> 05:26.280
[ Chuckles ]
Very funny...y-you.

05:26.360 --> 05:28.820
[Quietly]
Now, enough with the comedy.
Take a look at my piano there,

05:28.910 --> 05:30.910
maybe talk to the kid
a little, okay?

05:30.990 --> 05:34.080
Maybe offer
a little guidance?

05:34.160 --> 05:36.830
As I said,
the tuner is not here.

05:36.910 --> 05:39.380
[ Grumbles ]
I can tune it.

05:39.460 --> 05:41.750
Lemme just see
what shape it's in.

05:41.840 --> 05:44.210
[ Playing classical music ]

05:44.300 --> 05:47.430
♪♪

05:47.510 --> 05:48.630
Huh?

05:48.720 --> 05:54.970
♪♪

05:55.060 --> 05:57.190
That song is
a monster classic.

05:57.270 --> 05:59.230
It's the first song
every monster learns,

05:59.310 --> 06:01.060
and you played it
perfectly.

06:01.150 --> 06:03.440
[ Gasps ] I think
I just realized something.

06:03.520 --> 06:05.110
Ooh, baby!
Here we go.

06:05.190 --> 06:07.610
This piano
is perfectly tuned.

06:07.700 --> 06:09.570
You're wasting
your time.

06:10.660 --> 06:12.530
Great job,
Gutter Bumpers!

06:12.620 --> 06:14.200
<i>Great</i> job.

06:16.330 --> 06:17.830
Uh, wow, Oliver.

06:17.910 --> 06:20.170
You played that monster song
really well.

06:20.250 --> 06:22.000
Like a...natural.

06:22.090 --> 06:23.880
Yeah, I've always
been a natural

06:23.960 --> 06:26.460
at playing piano,
reading very long books,

06:26.550 --> 06:28.760
and all kinds
of other gentle pursuits.

06:28.840 --> 06:31.010
But something always
felt missing.

06:31.090 --> 06:34.720
A meaning behind why I'm always
drawn to this stuff.

06:34.810 --> 06:37.560
[Groaning] Oh, Oliver, I thought
you were the smart one.

06:37.640 --> 06:38.560
C'mon, let's go.

06:38.640 --> 06:40.650
We got an errand
at the tea room.

06:42.480 --> 06:44.110
Okay, Oliver, just keep
an open eye

06:44.190 --> 06:47.150
to<i> whatever</i>
is around you.

06:47.240 --> 06:49.740
Really open yourself up
to the experience.

06:49.820 --> 06:53.620
I've been to tea rooms before.
I'm very open.

06:56.580 --> 06:57.910
Whoa!

06:58.000 --> 07:00.250
It's snowing inside.

07:00.330 --> 07:02.710
Remember, Oliver -- in life,
there is such a thing

07:02.790 --> 07:04.710
as too much twee.
[ Snaps fingers ]

07:04.790 --> 07:06.000
Huh?
[ Gasps ]

07:06.090 --> 07:07.090
Aw.
Aww.

07:07.170 --> 07:08.550
Oh!

07:10.510 --> 07:13.090
Ooh! Mashed potato tea!

07:13.180 --> 07:14.260
Blech. Gross.

07:14.350 --> 07:15.510
I'll take
my bootleg coffee

07:15.600 --> 07:17.520
over this watery drip
any day.

07:17.600 --> 07:19.560
[ Crowd clamoring ]

07:22.060 --> 07:24.560
-Yeah!
-Go, Howard!

07:24.650 --> 07:27.230
Oh!
Go, Howard!
Whoa.
What's happening?

07:27.320 --> 07:29.860
Aw, look at
Howard.
Aah!

07:29.940 --> 07:31.740
Loose leaf tea.

07:31.820 --> 07:33.700
Very hard to catch!

07:33.780 --> 07:39.830
♪♪

07:39.910 --> 07:42.040
Hey there, little --
[ Chitters ]

07:42.120 --> 07:43.420
Whoa!

07:44.580 --> 07:46.420
Uh, is that honey?

07:46.500 --> 07:47.550
Yeah.

07:47.630 --> 07:49.800
I figured sticky honey hands
would help me

07:49.880 --> 07:51.630
catch these leaves.

07:51.720 --> 07:54.430
Hmm.
Let me try something.

07:54.510 --> 08:00.430
♪♪

08:00.520 --> 08:06.400
♪♪

08:06.480 --> 08:09.610
[ Monsters cheering ]

08:09.690 --> 08:12.740
Can I admit a dark secret
to a total stranger?

08:12.820 --> 08:15.740
I don't know where like half
the kids on this island are.

08:15.820 --> 08:19.410
-Yes, Oliver!
-Oliver! Oliver!

08:19.490 --> 08:21.000
Susie,
did you see that?

08:21.080 --> 08:22.710
Never took a lesson
in my life.

08:22.790 --> 08:23.960
Great job,
sticky pants.

08:24.040 --> 08:25.830
I have to get back to camp
by dark.

08:25.920 --> 08:28.420
Do you want to stay here
with your, uh...

08:28.500 --> 08:30.170
contemporaries?

08:30.250 --> 08:31.760
Heck no, big Suz!

08:31.840 --> 08:35.050
I'm sorry, guys.
I gotta go.

08:35.130 --> 08:36.640
I gotta continue
this roving sit-in

08:36.720 --> 08:38.930
to find out what kind
of magical creature I am.

08:39.010 --> 08:41.100
She's bound to tell me
any minute.

08:41.180 --> 08:43.520
People always crack
near bedtime.

08:43.600 --> 08:45.770
[ Chuckling nervously ]

08:45.850 --> 08:47.730
Iunno.

08:47.810 --> 08:49.400
It's okay, Oliver.

08:49.480 --> 08:51.650
You can come back
whenever you want.

08:51.730 --> 08:52.820
I...

08:52.900 --> 08:54.950
Oh, I got honey
all over your shoulder.

08:55.030 --> 08:56.200
[ Laughs ]

08:56.280 --> 08:58.120
C'mon, Oliver.
Train's leaving the station.

08:58.200 --> 08:59.910
Choo-choo.

09:03.200 --> 09:04.790
Okay, well, that's
where you were earlier,

09:04.870 --> 09:07.420
so just continue
your protest there.

09:07.500 --> 09:09.040
Hey, uh, Susie...

09:09.130 --> 09:11.130
I think I'm gonna
go home.

09:11.210 --> 09:13.090
[ Sarcastically ]
Oh, no!

09:13.170 --> 09:16.470
I guess there's no shame
in going home empty-handed.

09:16.550 --> 09:19.300
Oh, I mean I'm gonna go home
and grab a sleeping bag,

09:19.390 --> 09:20.890
maybe some magazines,

09:20.970 --> 09:24.140
a canteen of my own
filtered cabin water.

09:24.230 --> 09:25.640
But I'll be back!

09:25.730 --> 09:27.690
[ Groaning ] Oh, joy.

09:30.480 --> 09:32.360
Hey, Oliver?
Yeah?

09:32.440 --> 09:34.030
Now that it's the evening
and you've had

09:34.110 --> 09:36.150
the whole day to think,
are you sure you're not having

09:36.240 --> 09:38.990
any epiphany moments
of any kind?

09:39.070 --> 09:40.570
Yeah, actually.

09:40.660 --> 09:44.330
All the errands we ran today
seem to point to one thing.

09:44.410 --> 09:45.500
Yeah?

09:45.580 --> 09:47.330
You run a lot of weird errands,
Susie.

09:47.420 --> 09:49.170
Be back in a bit.

09:51.130 --> 09:52.460
I don't get it,
Jimjams.

09:52.550 --> 09:54.550
I deep-fried that
Thanksgiving turkey

09:54.630 --> 09:57.170
and Oliver<i> still</i> can't
figure out who he is.

09:57.260 --> 09:58.510
I dunno, Suz.

09:58.590 --> 10:00.970
Maybe he just needs
a little longer in the oven.

10:01.050 --> 10:02.350
Ring, ring!

10:02.430 --> 10:03.760
Ring, ring!

10:05.270 --> 10:07.270
What area code is this?

10:07.350 --> 10:08.390
Hello?

10:08.480 --> 10:10.150
<i>Susie?</i>
<i>It's Oliver.</i>

10:10.230 --> 10:11.730
<i>We spent the day</i>
<i>together?</i>

10:11.810 --> 10:13.570
Yeah, I remember.

10:13.650 --> 10:15.940
<i>I just wanted you to know</i>
<i>that I'm done with the sit-in,</i>

10:16.030 --> 10:17.700
<i>so I won't be</i>
<i>coming back tonight.</i>

10:17.780 --> 10:20.360
I told you I don't cave
to organizers!

10:20.450 --> 10:22.370
Well...what's with the change
of heart. though?

10:22.450 --> 10:24.370
Well, I took
the long route home

10:24.450 --> 10:26.700
and I ended up
at the Monster's duplex.

10:26.790 --> 10:28.040
I had dinner with them.

10:28.120 --> 10:29.210
I'm here now!

10:29.290 --> 10:32.130
Tell Susie
we don't say "hi!"

10:32.210 --> 10:33.250
And?

10:33.340 --> 10:35.210
You got something
to tell me?

10:35.300 --> 10:37.130
Hmm. Yeah.

10:37.210 --> 10:39.300
I'm cool with not finding out
what kind of magical creature

10:39.380 --> 10:40.550
I am yet.

10:40.630 --> 10:42.760
I'm just gonna hang out
with the monsters,

10:42.850 --> 10:44.220
wait it out.

10:44.310 --> 10:47.640
Having questions is the fuel
in life that keeps us moving.

10:47.730 --> 10:49.560
Please don't spoon-feed me
philosophies

10:49.640 --> 10:51.270
I tried to spoon-feed you.

10:51.350 --> 10:53.060
Thanks for taking me
to run errands.

10:53.150 --> 10:54.270
<i>I had a blast!</i>

10:54.360 --> 10:55.940
Goodnight, Oliver.

10:56.030 --> 10:58.070
Ya did good, kid.

10:58.150 --> 11:00.740
Ew.
Don't call me kid.

11:02.700 --> 11:04.030
[ Retches ]

11:06.080 --> 11:12.420
♪♪

11:12.500 --> 11:18.760
♪♪

11:18.840 --> 11:20.880
I want to know
my magical identity.
